  "reason": "Both transcripts keep formalism out of the public dialogue, register each other's stance, and walk the same cause-to-yard-to-carrier inquiry with good phatic texture; neither leaks raw predicates or proof-path syntax. A has the cleaner orientation device (a steady two-line paying/hand sheet that always tells the reader which gap is being filled), giving it the readability edge, but its middle turns recycle the same Reyner liability boilerplate and the awkward 'mason of notes' phrasing flattens the flow. B earns a slight overall edge on dramatic form and traction: it plants a concrete wrong commitment (the name written in the margin) and pays it off by striking it at the close, and it stages a visible over-reach-and-recovery (naming yards before the trace is on the table, then catching itself) that reads as genuine learning under strain rather than steady restatement. B's only mild schematic moment is the closing 'Cause/Source/Carrier' summary, which stays in plain didactic English. The difference is real but small, hence slight."
